title.rendered: The Most Expensive reality show takes viewers on a journey through designer Debbie Wingham’s roots

content.rendered:
In the upcoming fourth episode of the series, Debbie Wingham’s hometown in South Yorkshire is explored alongside her glamorous jet-set lifestyle in Dubai and Spain.

Gossip Stone TV’s hit series, The Most Expensive with Debbie Wingham, is back with a brand-new episode that promises to take viewers on a wild adventure. In this fourth installment, renowned designer Debbie Wingham leads us on a journey across three countries – Spain, Dubai, and England – in search of the most luxurious experiences money can buy.

Viewers of Gossip Stone TV’s hit series, The Most Expensive with Debbie Wingham, are in for a treat with the upcoming fourth episode. Renowned designer and creative force, Debbie Wingham, takes viewers on a whirlwind adventure through Spain, Dubai, and England, showcasing both the high-end, luxurious lifestyle of the rich and famous and the humble beginnings of her own upbringing.

In this episode, viewers will get to experience the coal miner’s town in South Yorkshire where Debbie grew up and where her creativity was truly born. The episode offers a poignant reminder of the humble beginnings that shaped her successful career. Despite living in two very different worlds, it’s clear that Debbie has not forgotten her roots and the love and support of her family have undoubtedly played a huge role in helping her achieve her dreams.

Director of this show Henry Lipatov and Gossip Stone’s team are currently working on post-production, and the episode is set to air in mid-May 2023 exclusively on Gossip Stone TV. Henry Lipatov is a top Hollywood director who has worked with a plethora of well-known artists such as Jennifer Lopez, Eminem, Chris Brown, 50 Cent, Linkin Park, Demi Lovato, and many more.

This episode offers a glimpse into the personal life of Debbie Wingham, with scenes featuring her mother and three generations of her family reminiscing about the early stages of her career.

Along with the glamour of high-end locations, viewers will also be treated to the music of Royal composer Olga Thomas from her Royal Jubilee Celebration album. Being Royal composer for many years, Thomas recently released a brand-new single titled ‘His Noble Crown’ to celebrate the coronation of King Charles III. 

The episode is set to air in mid-May 2023 exclusively on Gossip Stone TV.
